# Layman App — Cursor Rules

## Core Rules
- This is a React Native Expo app (not a web app). Use RN components only.
- Font family: ALWAYS use `PlusJakartaSans_500Medium`, `PlusJakartaSans_700Bold`, or `PlusJakartaSans_800ExtraBold`
- Color primary: `#D97B47` (orange), background: `#FAF4F0` (cream)
- Styles go in separate `*.styles.js` files, never inline beyond trivial cases
- Use Ionicons from `@expo/vector-icons` for all icons

## Article Structure
All articles must conform to:
```js
{
  id: string,           // unique identifier
  headline: string,     // 7-9 words, conversational tone
  image: string,        // URL
  content: string[],    // exactly 3 elements (swipeable cards)
  originalHeadline: string,
  originalContent: string,
  source: string,
  url: string,
  publishedAt: string
}
```

## AI Chat Rules
- Backend at `process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL` (frontend) or port 5000 (local)
- All Gemini responses: exactly 1-2 sentences in simple English
- Suggestions: always 3, generated dynamically from article context

## Supabase Rules
- Client in `frontend/src/utils/supabase.js`
- Use `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` and `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
- RLS is enabled — always pass user_id in queries
- saved_articles: unique constraint on (user_id, article_id)
